claim.claim-text:
20. A method of treating body lumens using a stent having a plurality of adjacently arranged rings connected to each other by at least one link defined by open loops extending generally parallel to a longitudinal axis of the stent, comprising: 
applying a force to reduce a diameter of the stent; 
configuring the stent so that the link is compressed to a smaller dimension; 
placing the stent on a catheter; 
inserting the catheter within a body lumen; and 
deploying the stent within the body lumen.
